<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Challenge 6: Tickets</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <a href="/dashboard"><< Back to Hub</a>
        <h1>Challenge 6: Client-Side Validation Bypass</h1>
        <div class="card">
            <p>The attackers have set up a fake ticket shop for the BBQ. You need to buy a VIP ticket to get the final flag.</p>
            <p>Problem: You have 0 credits, and the ticket costs 50 credits. Can you manipulate the request to get it for free?</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h3>BBQ Ticket Shop</h3>
            <p>Your Credits: <strong>0</strong></p>
            
            <% if (error) { %>
                <div class="error"><%= error %></div>
            <% } else if (flag) { %>
                <div class="success">Ticket Purchased! Here is your flag: <%= flag %></div>
            <% } %>

            <form action="/challenge/6/buy" method="POST">
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label>Item: VIP BBQ Ticket</label>
                    <input type="hidden" name="item" value="VIP Ticket">
                </div>
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label>Price: 50 Credits</label>
                    <!-- Is trusting the client with the price a good idea? -->
                    <input type="hidden" name="price" value="50">
                </div>
                <button type="submit">Buy Ticket</button>
            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
